.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- our final project for the sprint! - a simple UNIX command interpreter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a minimal command-line interpreter implemented as a learning project.
It reads commands from standard input and executes them using the system PATH.

This shell supports basic command execution and a small set of built-ins.
.SH OPTIONS
This shell currently accepts no command-line options.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.
.SH USAGE
Run the shell and enter commands at the prompt:

.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ echo "hello"
.fi
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on normal exit. Errors return a non-zero value where applicable.
.SH ERRORS
Error messages are written to standard error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Used to locate executable commands.
.SH FILES
None.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ pwd
$ env
.fi
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Andrew Kasapidis.
.SH BUGS
This shell is intentionally minimal and does not support advanced features
such as pipes, redirection, or job control. We're only in verion 0.1!
